results.name: Smaller factor of the n-th semiprime of the form (m!)^2+1.
link: Hugo Pfoertner, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..17
formula: Numbers p such that p*q = (A083340(n)!)^2 + 1, p, q prime, p < q.
xref: Cf. A020549, A083340, subsequence of A282706.
results.author: _Hugo Pfoertner_, Apr 25 2003
ext: The 11th term of the sequence (49-digit factor of the 100 digit number (41!)^2+1 was found with Yuji Kida's multiple polynomial quadratic sieve UBASIC PPMPQS v3.5 in 13 days CPU time on an Intel PIII 550 MHz.
Missing a(4) and new a(14), a(15) added by _Hugo Pfoertner_, Jul 13 2019
